"{\"uid\": \"cnn.com-2024-07-04-sport-jesse-owens-grandson-1936-olympics-berlin-spt-intl\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Follow:  AmericanJesse Owens'achievements at the 1936 Olympics in Berlin - he won four gold medals in the 100 meters, the 200m, the 4x100m relay and the long jump - made him a track and field great.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 72, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999999321057681, \"rank\": 6.786889919730236e-08, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those achievements came under the gaze of Adolf Hitler, who had initially planned for the Olympics held in Nazi Germany to showcase what he believed to be the racial superiority of\\u00a0White, so-called \\\"Aryan\\\"\\u00a0athletes, openly denigrating Black American participants as \\\"non-humans.\\\"\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1941034643349247e-26, \"text\": \"Adolf Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}, {\"begin\": 307, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.5756330042137927, \"rank\": 0.6975126740186345, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aryan_race\", \"score\": 0.9977532738009072, \"rank\": 0.002240983718145693, \"text\": \"Aryan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aryan_race\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aryan_race\"}, {\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.9983045976663941, \"rank\": 0.001698281603983405, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999986178454948, \"rank\": 1.3813340685839883e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The image of Owens - one of 18 Black athletes on the US team - atop the podium and surrounded by individuals giving the Nazi salute\\u00a0has become part of Olympic lore.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 534, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998532863615691, \"rank\": 0.0001372304218337076, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_salute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nazi salute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_salute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_salute\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens' grandson Stuart Owen Rankin describes the track and field great's actions as a \\\"thumb in the eye\\\" to Hitler.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Stuart\", \"score\": 0.9996514594001025, \"rank\": 0.00034866126745284514, \"text\": \"Stuart\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Stuart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Stuart\"}, {\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}, {\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.437848785093362e-14, \"text\": \"Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My grandfather's legacy continues to prosper.\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When people do find out and it's not often that I discuss it outwardly, but people do eventually find out, for example, perhaps through watching interviews like this, their response is always positive,\\\" Rankin told CNN's Don Riddell.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999999405940816, \"rank\": 5.940597737886461e-08, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}, {\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Don_Draper\", \"score\": 0.9911847901944675, \"rank\": 0.0088936088227737, \"text\": \"Don\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Don_Draper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Don_Draper\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riddell_Sports_Group\", \"score\": 0.9999999760852919, \"rank\": 2.3914487205165936e-08, \"text\": \"Riddell\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riddell_Sports_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riddell_Sports_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Their response is one that fills me with pride.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Again, their response speaks to my grandfather's accomplishments and the enduring quality of what he did in '36 and sort of the timelessness of those accomplishments.\\\"\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another enduring memory from the 1936 Games was Owens'\\u00a0connection with the German long-jumper Luz Long.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9991847401321834, \"rank\": 0.0007478549267798427, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens and Long were seen as the two favorites to compete for the gold medal in the long jump at the Berlin Games.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The two men came from very different backgrounds.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens was a Black American and Long was a White German living in Nazi Germany.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.9983045976663941, \"rank\": 0.001698281603983405, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1552, \"end\": 1560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999986178454948, \"rank\": 1.3813340685839883e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.5756330042137927, \"rank\": 0.6975126740186345, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.5756330042137927, \"rank\": 0.6975126740186345, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given the circumstances of the 1936 Olympics, a level of hostility might have been expected between the long jumpers.\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, the opposite was true.\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Rankin,\\u00a0Owens said Long offered him advice\\u00a0on how to not overstep, which was an issue the US athlete was having in the long jump qualifying competition.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1778, \"end\": 1784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}, {\"begin\": 1868, \"end\": 1870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998532863615691, \"rank\": 0.0001372304218337076, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following Long's advice, Owens\\u00a0said he\\u00a0put down a towel at a mark to help him perfect his run-up and in doing so, the American was able to successfully book his spot in the long-jump final.\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 2121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999986178454948, \"rank\": 1.3813340685839883e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens went on to claim gold, while Long secured the silver.\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It took a lot of courage for [Long] to befriend me in front of Hitler,\\\" Owens later said of his friendship with Long.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.437848785093362e-14, \"text\": \"Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can melt down all the medals and cups I have and they would not be a plating on the 24-carat friendship I felt for Long at that moment.\\\"\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rankin says the two became \\\"comrades, became allies, became friends\\\" by pushing themselves to greater heights.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What came from that was a bond, a brotherhood, a connection between two world class athletes on the highest stage of their particular event or sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Long was killed fighting for Nazi Germany in World War II, but the families of the Americn and German still remain in contact, bonded through their grandfathers' friendship, according to Rankin.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2739, \"end\": 2751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.5756330042137927, \"rank\": 0.6975126740186345, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9991847401321834, \"rank\": 0.0007478549267798427, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens' grandson recalls traveling to Munich for business and a colleague, upon finding out who his grandfather was, asked if he knew who Long was.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 3052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"score\": 0.9995287010093747, \"rank\": 0.0004705333846726458, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once they had established that he did, Rankin's colleague scrolled through his contacts' list and found the name Julia Long,\\u00a0the German long jumper's granddaughter.\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3093, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}, {\"begin\": 3167, \"end\": 3172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"score\": 0.9999999999522515, \"rank\": 4.735874917514086e-11, \"text\": \"Julia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\"}, {\"begin\": 3183, \"end\": 3189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9991847401321834, \"rank\": 0.0007478549267798427, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Through that connection, Rankin and Long's granddaughter met for dinner, an evening he describes as a \\\"very special meal, a very special conversation.\\\"\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We both spoke to what it was like to be the grandchild of an Olympian, particularly an Olympian from those Games and particularly our respective grandfathers and only Julia could speak to what it's like in a way that's similar to how I could speak to what it's like,\\\" remembers Rankin.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3435, \"end\": 3443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999998826752, \"rank\": 1.1718249516357662e-10, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 3461, \"end\": 3469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999998826752, \"rank\": 1.1718249516357662e-10, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 3541, \"end\": 3546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"score\": 0.9999999999522515, \"rank\": 4.735874917514086e-11, \"text\": \"Julia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\"}, {\"begin\": 3652, \"end\": 3658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And so, we of course bonded over that.\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We talked about our personal interests that are likely to have been influenced by our grandfathers, our interests in outdoors and physicality and sports.\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it was, it was a very special time and a very special conversation and the connection continues on today.\\\"\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Berlin Games,\\u00a0widespread, institutionalized racism and segregation in the US\\u00a0meant Owens'\\u00a0achievements were not fully appreciated\\u00a0when he returned home.\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 4128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4050, \"end\": 4052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998532863615691, \"rank\": 0.0001372304218337076, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the then-22-year-old Owens did receive a New York ticker tape parade, he was forced to ride in a freight elevator to a reception in his honor at the Waldorf Astoria\\u00a0hotel.\", \"from\": 4130, \"to\": 4310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4180, \"end\": 4188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999993262065342, \"rank\": 6.737927282061741e-07, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 4288, \"end\": 4303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waldorf_Astoria_New_York\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.790122039894237e-38, \"text\": \"Waldorf Astoria\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q27686\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waldorf_Astoria_New_York\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waldorf_Astoria_New_York\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Although I wasn't invited to shake hands with Hitler,\\\" Owens said, \\\"I wasn't invited to the White House to shake hands with the President, either.\\\"\", \"from\": 4312, \"to\": 4460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4359, \"end\": 4365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.437848785093362e-14, \"text\": \"Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}, {\"begin\": 4405, \"end\": 4416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"score\": 0.9999999999395186, \"rank\": 6.053006238293676e-11, \"text\": \"White House\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens also failed to attract the endorsements and sponsorship deals enjoyed by White athletes, and was reduced to running exhibition races against\\u00a0motorbikes and\\u00a0horses to make ends meet.\", \"from\": 4462, \"to\": 4649, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was not until the 1950s, 20 years after his Berlin triumph, that he finally achieved a measure of financial security, opening a public relations firm and becoming a highly successful public speaker.\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4698, \"end\": 4704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999999321057681, \"rank\": 6.786889919730236e-08, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens later received the two highest civilian honors the US can bestow.\", \"from\": 4854, \"to\": 4925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4911, \"end\": 4913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998532863615691, \"rank\": 0.0001372304218337076, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1976, he received the Presidential Medal of Freedom from Gerald Ford,\\u00a0and in 1990, a decade after his death from lung cancer, President George\\u00a0H.W.\", \"from\": 4926, \"to\": 5076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4986, \"end\": 4992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1843669479411247e-14, \"text\": \"Gerald\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\"}, {\"begin\": 4993, \"end\": 4997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"score\": 0.9999999999790816, \"rank\": 2.0727695721329327e-11, \"text\": \"Ford\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bush\\u00a0presented his widow\\u00a0a posthumous Congressional\\u00a0Gold Medal.\", \"from\": 5077, \"to\": 5140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In perhaps the most fitting memorial to his achievements, a street in Berlin was renamed in his honor in 1984.\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5212, \"end\": 5218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999999321057681, \"rank\": 6.786889919730236e-08, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked what the reception would be for Owens upon his return to the US had he achieved his feats in 2024, Rankin\\u00a0says\\u00a0his grandfather would \\\"recognize \\u2026 almost immeasurable strides in progress in terms of race relations here within the United States.\\\"\", \"from\": 5254, \"to\": 5504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5321, \"end\": 5323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998532863615691, \"rank\": 0.0001372304218337076, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5359, \"end\": 5365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"score\": 0.9999139468102464, \"rank\": 8.606059566452203e-05, \"text\": \"Rankin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Rankin\"}, {\"begin\": 5489, \"end\": 5502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999987648069134, \"rank\": 1.2308791178262128e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Rankin added that there are \\\"still people, many people, people in pow